<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">
It is the type species of the monotypic genus that is known from the single taxonomic entry. In order to provide more detailed data about its morphology, we provide SEM images of its male palp and epigyne have been presented. The original figures by 
<bibRefCitation author="Eskov, KY" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" refId="B2" refString="Eskov, KY, 1989. New monotypic genera of the spider family Linyphiidae (Aranei) from Siberia: Communication 1. Zoologicheskiĭ Zhurnal 68(9): 68-78. [In Russian with English summary]." title="New monotypic genera of the spider family Linyphiidae (Aranei) from Siberia: Communication 1. Zoologicheskiĭ Zhurnal 68 (9): 68 - 78. [In Russian with English summary]." year="1989">Eskov (1989)</bibRefCitation>
do not show the complex shape of the radix as if having only a single apophysis, despite it having a small posterior (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Rp</emphasis>
) and a larger anterior (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Ra</emphasis>
) apophyses and a very short tailpiece (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Tp</emphasis>
). Numerous fine teeth on the terminal part of the suprategular apophysis (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Sa</emphasis>
) were not shown as well as the large median membrane (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Mm</emphasis>
). The epigyne in light microscope (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Copulatory organs of Kolymocyba petrophila (A-C, F-H) and Walckenaeria microspiralis (D-E, I). A - C terminal part of male palp, prolateral, antero-prolateral and ventral; D, F whole male palp, retrolateral; E whole male palp, dorso-retrolateral showing dorsal tibial apophysis; G-I epigyne, ventral. Scale = 0.1 mm if not otherwise indicated. Abbreviations: Em - embolus, Mm - median membrane, Ra - anterior radix apophysis, Rp - posterior radix apophysis, Sa - suprategular apophysis, Tp - tailpiece of embolic division." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489779" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">6H</figureCitation>
) looks like the one illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Eskov, KY" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" refId="B2" refString="Eskov, KY, 1989. New monotypic genera of the spider family Linyphiidae (Aranei) from Siberia: Communication 1. Zoologicheskiĭ Zhurnal 68(9): 68-78. [In Russian with English summary]." title="New monotypic genera of the spider family Linyphiidae (Aranei) from Siberia: Communication 1. Zoologicheskiĭ Zhurnal 68 (9): 68 - 78. [In Russian with English summary]." year="1989">Eskov (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. This species and genus are new to Kamchatka. It was known from Magadan Area (
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, YM" journalOrPublisher="Korean Arachnology" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" pagination="129 - 158" refId="B8" refString="Marusik, YM, Eskov, KY, Kim, JP, 1992. A check-list of spiders (Aranei) of Northeast Asia. Korean Arachnology 8 (1-2): 129 - 158" title="A check-list of spiders (Aranei) of Northeast Asia." volume="8" year="1992">Marusik et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mikhailov, KG" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" pagination="1 - 264" refId="B16" refString="Mikhailov, KG, 2013. The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist. Arthropoda Selecta, Supplement 3: 1 - 264" title="The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist." volume="3" year="2013">Mikhailov 2013</bibRefCitation>
) only and the record from Kamchatka lies at the south-easternmost limit of its range.
</paragraph>
